<figureCitation id="3186EA8E2103262367C24F74E2A55B0A" box="[750,766,1876,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1287,1309]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,281,1262]" captionTargetId="figure-64@2.[151,1436,281,1262]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–E. Begonia microinduta M.D.Miranda. A, Habit; B, Apical bud, showing stipule indumentum; C, Immature flower buds; D, Seedlings on rock in the natural habitat; E, Upper portion of the petiole, showing microscopic trichomes. (Scale Bars:A= 7 cm; B= 2.5 cm; C= 5 mm; D= 10 mm; E= 15 mm) (A–E from M.D. Miranda 11)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423820" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423820/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2</figureCitation>
