<emphasis id="9BC92A1921012621662D4D27E34A5978" bold="true" box="[769,785,1287,1308]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">B</emphasis>
, Apical bud, showing stipule indumentum; 
<emphasis id="9BC92A1921012621619F4D27E49F5979" bold="true" box="[1203,1220,1287,1309]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">C</emphasis>
, Immature flower buds; 
<emphasis id="9BC92A192101262165A44D0BE0C25924" bold="true" box="[136,153,1323,1344]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">D</emphasis>
, Seedlings on rock in the natural habitat; 
<emphasis id="9BC92A1921012621670A4D0BE26D5924" bold="true" box="[550,566,1323,1344]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">E</emphasis>
, Upper portion of the petiole, showing microscopic trichomes. (Scale Bars: A= 7 cm; B= 2.5 cm; C= 5 mm; D= 10 mm; E= 15 mm) (
<emphasis id="9BC92A192101262167264D6FE2635900" bold="true" box="[522,568,1359,1380]" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">A–E</emphasis>
from 
<emphasis id="9BC92A1921012621675E4D70E3425900" box="[626,793,1359,1381]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="51">M.D. Miranda 11</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
